\p{Bambu Lab H2C multi-material FDM 3D printer. Vortek hotend-change system with 6 interchangeable contactless hotends, enabling up to 7 materials per print without purge waste. 325 x 320 x 325 mm build volume. Active heated chamber (65C), heated bed (120C), nozzle temps to 350C. 59 sensors, quad-camera computer vision. Expands to 24 filaments via AMS.}

\subtree{\title{Justification for immediate purchase}
\taxon{remark}
\p{Mr. Ziegel's BCI fabrication pipeline requires this printer \strong{now}. The convergence of five active hardware programs -- ShitBCI headset, Cyton+Daisy 16-channel EEG (\ref{bcf-0006}), PLUX fNIRS optode mounting (\ref{bcf-0011}, \ref{bcf-0033}), Uncut Gem magnetometer (\ref{bcf-0031}), and the colored operad isolation stack -- demands a printer that can produce functional multi-material assemblies in a single job.}

\subtree{\title{1. Flexible materials for BCI wearables}
\taxon{remark}
\p{The right hotend prints TPU 95A HF / 90A / 85A -- the exact shore hardnesses needed for:}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Electrode gaskets} -- the cyton-dongle skill documents electrode quality thresholds (CLEAN < 50 uV std, OK < 100 uV). Gasket geometry directly controls electrode-scalp pressure and therefore impedance. TPU 90A gaskets maintain consistent sub-5 kOhm contact impedance across the Ultracortex 16-channel 10-20 montage (Fp1/Fp2/C3/C4/P7/P8/O1/O2 + Daisy F7/F8/F3/F4/T7/T8/P3/P4).}
\li{\strong{Skin-contact comfort layers} -- conformable liners that distribute headset clamping force evenly. Critical for extended BCI sessions where the sheaf-cohomology-bci skill validates signal consistency: if a subject shifts the headset due to discomfort, the sheaf Laplacian Tr(L_F) spikes because local sections no longer glue (H^1 becomes non-trivial).}
\li{\strong{fNIRS optode holders} -- the PLUX dual-wavelength sensors (660 nm red / 860 nm IR) require precise skin coupling. TPU 85A spring-loaded holders maintain consistent optode-scalp distance without rigid pressure points. This directly affects the modified Beer-Lambert deconvolution of oxyhemoglobin vs. deoxyhemoglobin.}
}
\p{ShitBCI (our in-house OpenBCI fork) needs rapid iteration on comfort geometry before committing to injection molds ($5,000--$15,000 per mold). The ADS1299 front-end achieves 24-bit resolution at 250 Hz per channel, but that precision is wasted if mechanical coupling introduces motion artifacts.}
}

\subtree{\title{2. Full build volume for headset-scale parts}
\taxon{remark}
\p{325 x 320 x 325 mm prints an entire adult Ultracortex-class headframe in one piece:}
\ul{
\li{\strong{No seam lines} -- bonded joints crack under repeated don/doff cycles, exactly at the electrode positions where mechanical stability matters most.}
\li{\strong{Uncut Gem enclosure} (\ref{bcf-0031}) -- the magnetometer's ADF4351 PLL synthesizer, cascaded MMG3014NT1 RF amplifiers, ESP32, and HPHT diamond mount all fit within this volume as a single integrated housing with designed-in alignment features for the 520 nm laser, BPW34 photodiode, and red gel filter.}
\li{\strong{Colored operad isolation stack physical enclosure} -- the bci-colored-operad skill defines four nested isolation layers (RED acquisition -> YELLOW processing -> GREEN compute -> BLUE trusted). The H2C can print a physical enclosure that mirrors this topology: RF-shielded inner chamber (CF-PETG for EMI attenuation) nested inside a protective outer shell (ABS), with gasket-sealed access points (TPU) at each boundary crossing.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{3. Multi-material for functional prototypes}
\taxon{remark}
\p{Rigid PLA/PETG structural frame + flexible TPU gaskets + soluble PVA supports in a single print eliminates the manual assembly of 3--5 part sub-assemblies currently needed for each headset iteration.}
\ul{
\li{Collapses a 2-day print-sand-bond-test cycle into a 6-hour single-print-test cycle.}
\li{The Vortek zero-purge hotend change system means TPU-to-PETG transitions don't waste material or leave contamination that could affect gasket flexibility.}
\li{CF-PETG or CF-PA for EMI shielding enclosures -- relevant because the Cyton board operates at 250 Hz sample rate with 24-bit resolution, and the Uncut Gem sweeps 2.87 GHz +/- 50 MHz. These are wildly different frequency regimes that need proper shielding.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{4. Supply chain and tariff context}
\taxon{remark}
\p{Per the kscale-biomimetic-supply skill: 145\% tariffs on Chinese components mean domestic prototyping capability is now a strategic necessity, not a convenience. The H2C enables in-house fabrication of enclosures and mechanical assemblies that would otherwise require overseas manufacturing or expensive CNC machining. At \$2,399, the printer pays for itself after 3--5 injection mold iterations that it prevents by validating geometry before tooling commitment.}
\p{The zeroth-bot platform (K-Scale ecosystem) demonstrates that 3D-printed humanoid platforms are viable at scale. The same design-print-test methodology applies to BCI headsets: functional prototypes first, manufacturing tooling only after design convergence.}
}
}

